Haematologica
    Aspirin in essential thrombocythemia: To whom? What formulation? What regimen?
Although additional data on gastrointestinal tolerability will be useful, the bid regimen could already be implemented in clinical practice, considering its favorable risk/benefit profile. However, patients whose platelet count has been normalized could still be treated with the od regimen, because they would otherwise be unnecessarily exposed to a potential small risk of gastrointestinal discomfort.
